{
  "doc_id": "12442",
  "text": "To the best of our knowledge, this is the first computational method linking genome-scale reconstructions of bacterial metabolism with food web bioaccumulation models for designing and analysing bioremediation strategies. Approaches based on high dimensional omics data and network inference methods [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] have been proposed for predicting the exposure of organisms to contaminated sites and for reconstructing adverse outcome pathways [CITATION_3] . From the experimental side, [CITATION_4] were the first to study how in situ sediment treatment reduces bioaccumulation at different trophic levels in aquatic food chains.",
